{"name":"Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Sites.InducedTopology","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Sites.DenseSubsite"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/InducedTopology.lean#L160-L163","name":"CategoryTheory.CoverDense.sheafEquiv","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/InducedTopology.html#CategoryTheory.CoverDense.sheafEquiv","doc":"Cover-dense functors induces an equivalence of categories of sheaves.\n\nThis is known as the comparison lemma. It requires that the sites are small and the value category\nis complete.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/InducedTopology.lean#L134-L142","name":"CategoryTheory.over_forget_locallyCoverDense","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/InducedTopology.html#CategoryTheory.over_forget_locallyCoverDense","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/InducedTopology.lean#L127-L129","name":"CategoryTheory.CoverDense.inducedTopology","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/InducedTopology.html#CategoryTheory.CoverDense.inducedTopology","doc":"Given a fully faithful cover-dense functor `G : C ⥤ (D, K)`, we may induce a topology on `C`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/InducedTopology.lean#L115-L122","name":"CategoryTheory.CoverDense.locallyCoverDense","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/InducedTopology.html#CategoryTheory.CoverDense.locallyCoverDense","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/InducedTopology.lean#L109-L110","name":"CategoryTheory.LocallyCoverDense.inducedTopology_coverPreserving","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/InducedTopology.html#CategoryTheory.LocallyCoverDense.inducedTopology_coverPreserving","doc":"`G` is cover-preserving wrt the induced topology. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/InducedTopology.lean#L104-L105","name":"CategoryTheory.LocallyCoverDense.inducedTopology_coverLifting","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/InducedTopology.html#CategoryTheory.LocallyCoverDense.inducedTopology_coverLifting","doc":"`G` is cover-lifting wrt the induced topology. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/InducedTopology.lean#L77-L100","name":"CategoryTheory.LocallyCoverDense.inducedTopology","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/InducedTopology.html#CategoryTheory.LocallyCoverDense.inducedTopology","doc":"If a functor `G : C ⥤ (D, K)` is fully faithful and locally dense,\nthen the set `{ T ∩ mor(C) | T ∈ K }` is a grothendieck topology of `C`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/InducedTopology.lean#L76-L76","name":"CategoryTheory.LocallyCoverDense.inducedTopology_sieves","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/InducedTopology.html#CategoryTheory.LocallyCoverDense.inducedTopology_sieves","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/InducedTopology.lean#L64-L70","name":"CategoryTheory.LocallyCoverDense.pushforward_cover_iff_cover_pullback","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/InducedTopology.html#CategoryTheory.LocallyCoverDense.pushforward_cover_iff_cover_pullback","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/InducedTopology.lean#L56-L57","name":"CategoryTheory.LocallyCoverDense","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/InducedTopology.html#CategoryTheory.LocallyCoverDense","doc":"We say that a functor `C ⥤ D` into a site is \"locally dense\" if\nfor each covering sieve `T` in `D`, `T ∩ mor(C)` generates a covering sieve in `D`.\n"}]}